org.rappsilber.utils

Interface SelfAdd<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FDRSelfAdd<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFDRElement, AsymmetricPSM, DirectionalPeptidePair, Peptide, PeptidePair, Protein, ProteinGroup, ProteinGroupDirectionalLink, ProteinGroupDirectionalPair, ProteinGroupLink, ProteinGroupPair, PSM

    public interface SelfAdd<T>
    A object can add another object of the same type to its self. Idea is, that links and protein interactions can be defined via different peptides. So if we have already the PPI defined we just add the new sources and scores to it.
